<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="8" bgcolor="#E9D7B9"><tr><td>
<font class="title">Our Mission and Charter</font><br><font class="content">FlameKeepers of Norrath<br><br><br><br><p align="justify">"..Tis the desire o' this Fellowship that these five words (Friendship, Laughter, Adventure, Mirth, Entertainment) combine ta create our code o' belief an' that our members come together as family ta uphold this code." </p><br><p align="justify">Here be some general knowledge o' our guild…
<br>
We are a role-playing guild, and while not mandatory, feel it adds to the ambience of the game if characters are publicly role-played. By this it is meant that all public actions, shouts, etc be kept 'in character' and use ooc, private tells, and personal conversation for non-role-playing discussions. 
<br><br>

Blind to class or race FlameKeepers of Norrath also disregards alignment (level requirement is currently 20). 'Evil' and 'good' characters are both welcome to join. Members are encouraged to work with the Council of Elders and fellow guild mates to create and schedule events, quests, and role-play scenarios for guild and non-guild members. While we enjoy all aspects of EverQuest, our primary goal is always to feed the FLAME. If you are strictly a power-leveler or Phat Lewt player - this is <b>not</b> the guild for you. 
<br><br>
<br>
PLEASE NOTE - You can access our <a href="http://www.flamekeepers.com/modules.php?name=Content&pa=showpage&pid=16">Raid & Loot Rules from here</a> for now. <br>
<br>
<b>Policy & Procedures </b>
<br>
We prefer not to hae so many rules an' while we feel that many o' these are 'common sense', we still felt several o' them worthwhile of explainin'.  <br><br>

1. It's a G-A-M-E - have fun!!  *smiles*
<br><br>
2. Wear our tag with pride. If ye cannae display it, we are not the clan fer ye. /Role is acceptable - /Anon is not. 
<br><br>
3. Understand an’ respect that by donnin’ the tag, ye no longer represent ye alone. Yer words an’ deeds now reflect the ENTIRE CLAN – act wit’ honor. 
<br><br>
4. Our motto is “Burn Bright” – learn it, love it, live it – USE IT. It be expected that when a guildmate enters the land, this call goes forth – on both sides.  (/gu Burn Bright! - Make a hotkey if ye need too! *winks*)
<br><br>
5. Members may belong to other guilds as well as FlameKeepers. 
<br><br>
6. Members may have as many characters as they wish tagged - names may be any they wish an’ need not be similar. To have “alt” chars tagged, submit an email to the CoE with both main an’ alt names. If you remove a character, please advise an Officer either via EMAIL or our boards. 
<br><br>
7. If a member will be absent from game/guild fer extended period o’ time, notification must be made an’ member will be put on LOA (Leave o’ Absence), unless a request is made to be removed from guild. Members not seen fer one month (without notification) will placed on MIA (Missin’ in Action) fer one month, moved to LOA fer one month an’ then removed from roster. Ye may be re-inducted upon return. 
<br><br>
8. While we be happy to help family & friends as we are able, bear in mind that yer fellow guildmates/players are here to enjoy the game as well. Do NOT badger fer assistance of any form (gear, levels, money, rides, etc). If someone can answer yer need, they will. If they are otherwise occupied or unable – respect that. In short, DO NOT BEG. Not from yer clan, not from others. 
<br><br>
9. Members do not engage in verbal sparrin’ via any chat channel (/say, /ooc, /shout, /auction, /custom chats, etc). Period. If ye run into an issue, vent to the guild or request assistance. If none is available, /log what ye can, act as an adult, an’ exit the situation. Seek out an officer if ye wish further action. 
<br><br>
10. Members engagin’ in foul ethics will immediately be removed from the guild. No ifs, ands, or buts. Foul ethics are unacceptable an’ include-an’ are not limited to-kill-stealing, abusive or excessive foul language, an’ disruption of another player's game enjoyment. "I was role-playing." is not a reasonable excuse. 
<br><br>
11. Text comes across differently than voice/body language. In the world o’ Norrath, we lack signals (voice tone, body language, facial expressions) that convey the true meanin’ o’ words. Ye may know what ye are typin’ is meant to be a joke, while another may take it very differently. Remember real people are behind these screens an’ as text does not reflect as true as voice – be careful of your words. 
<br><br>
12. We encourage members to speak freely on our private guild boards (meanin’ be as forthright as ye wish). However, on public boards think before ye ‘speak’. We are not here to police ye, nor infringe on yer opinions – only to ask that ye consider afore ye type. One final time, as it is the most important, typed text does NOT reflect as true as spoken word. Think before ye type. 
<br><br>
FKoN disciplinary actions follow a set path, dependin’ on the severity o’ each case: verbal warnin’, written warnin’, probation, suspension, an’ expulsion. Bannin’ will occur when persons become violent, rude, crude, or spam the boards in unfriendly manner.
<br><br>
Serious violations (such as Rules 8 an’ 9) will begin the procedure. Minor infringements (such as rules 2 an’ 4 bein’ disregarded) will merit verbal warnings (call it naggin’ if ye want but ye will be called on it). Should Rule 10 be broken, ye will be expelled an’ not eligible fer re-entry into FKoN. Other situations will warrant attention as they arise.
<br>
<br>
<b>Guild Meeting Protocol </b>
<br><br>

1. In circular formation, Elders will sit together with Advisors to either side of them and all Keepers helping to form the circle. 
<br><br>

2. Each Keeper shall bring & hold a torch during all meetings. Extra torches will be available to those without one of their own, but cannae be provided for all. Please bring yer own if at all possible. 
<br><br>

3. Guests are always welcome to attend meetings. Prior notice is welcome so that the ArchPriest/ess is aware and can greet appropriately. 
<br><br>

4. The center of the circle is reserved for Seekers(recruits), Initiates who will be formally inducted into the guild. Following inductions, the center will be used for promotions/titles, and for award distribution. At all other times the circle will remain unoccupied. 
<br><br>

5. Meetings will generally consist of the following: 
<br><br>

- Opening <br><br>


- Formal Inductions <br><br>


- Promotions/Title Bestowment <br><br>


- Awards <br><br>


- General Session & Announcements <br><br>


- Closing <br><br>


- Event - if scheduled 

</p><br><p align="justify"></p><br><br><br><br><br><center> </center><br><br><p align="right">Council of Elders<br />
